44CachedResourceRequest::CachedResourceRequest(ResourceRequest&& resourceRequest, const ResourceLoaderOptions& options, std::optional<ResourceLoadPriority> priority, String&& charset)
45 : m_resourceRequest(WTFMove(resourceRequest))
46 , m_charset(WTFMove(charset))
47 , m_options(options)
48 , m_priority(priority)
49 , m_fragmentIdentifier(splitFragmentIdentifierFromRequestURL(m_resourceRequest))
50{
51}
52
53String CachedResourceRequest::splitFragmentIdentifierFromRequestURL(ResourceRequest& request)
54{
55 if (!MemoryCache::shouldRemoveFragmentIdentifier(request.url()))
56 return { };
57 URL url = request.url();
58 auto fragmentIdentifier = url.fragmentIdentifier().toString();
59 url.removeFragmentIdentifier();
60 request.setURL(url);
61 return fragmentIdentifier;
62}

64void CachedResourceRequest::setInitiator(Element& element)
65{
66 ASSERT(!m_initiatorElement);
67 ASSERT(m_initiatorName.isEmpty());
68 m_initiatorElement = &element;
69}
70
71void CachedResourceRequest::setInitiator(const AtomString& name)
72{
73 ASSERT(!m_initiatorElement);
74 ASSERT(m_initiatorName.isEmpty());
75 m_initiatorName = name;
76}
77
78const AtomString& CachedResourceRequest::initiatorName() const
79{
80 if (m_initiatorElement)
81 return m_initiatorElement->localName();
82 if (!m_initiatorName.isEmpty())
83 return m_initiatorName;
84
85 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> defaultName("other", AtomString::ConstructFromLiteral);
86 return defaultName;
87}
88
89void CachedResourceRequest::updateForAccessControl(Document& document)
90{
91 ASSERT(m_options.mode == FetchOptions::Mode::Cors);
92
93 m_origin = &document.securityOrigin();
94 updateRequestForAccessControl(m_resourceRequest, *m_origin, m_options.storedCredentialsPolicy);
95}
96
97void upgradeInsecureResourceRequestIfNeeded(ResourceRequest& request, Document& document)
98{
99 URL url = request.url();
100
101 ASSERT(document.contentSecurityPolicy());
102 document.contentSecurityPolicy()->upgradeInsecureRequestIfNeeded(url, ContentSecurityPolicy::InsecureRequestType::Load);
103
104 if (url == request.url())
105 return;
106
107 request.setURL(url);
108}
109
110void CachedResourceRequest::upgradeInsecureRequestIfNeeded(Document& document)
111{
112 upgradeInsecureResourceRequestIfNeeded(m_resourceRequest, document);
113}

125static inline constexpr ASCIILiteral acceptHeaderValueForImageResource(bool supportsVideoImage)
126{
127#if HAVE(WEBP) || USE(WEBP)
128 #define WEBP_HEADER_PART "image/webp,"
129#else
130 #define WEBP_HEADER_PART ""
131#endif
132 if (supportsVideoImage)
133 return WEBP_HEADER_PART "image/png,image/svg+xml,image/*;q=0.8,video/*;q=0.8,*/*;q=0.5"_s;
134 return WEBP_HEADER_PART "image/png,image/svg+xml,image/*;q=0.8,*/*;q=0.5"_s;
135 #undef WEBP_HEADER_PART
136}
137
138String CachedResourceRequest::acceptHeaderValueFromType(CachedResource::Type type)
139{
140 switch (type) {
141 case CachedResource::Type::MainResource:
142 return "text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8"_s;
143 case CachedResource::Type::ImageResource:
144 return acceptHeaderValueForImageResource(ImageDecoder::supportsMediaType(ImageDecoder::MediaType::Video));
145 case CachedResource::Type::CSSStyleSheet:
146 return "text/css,*/*;q=0.1"_s;
147 case CachedResource::Type::SVGDocumentResource:
148 return "image/svg+xml"_s;
149#if ENABLE(XSLT)
150 case CachedResource::Type::XSLStyleSheet:
151 // FIXME: This should accept more general xml formats */*+xml, image/svg+xml for example.
152 return "text/xml,application/xml,application/xhtml+xml,text/xsl,application/rss+xml,application/atom+xml"_s;
153#endif
154 default:
155 return "*/*"_s;
156 }
157}
158
159void CachedResourceRequest::setAcceptHeaderIfNone(CachedResource::Type type)
160{
161 if (!m_resourceRequest.hasHTTPHeader(HTTPHeaderName::Accept))
162 m_resourceRequest.setHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::Accept, acceptHeaderValueFromType(type));
163}
164
165void CachedResourceRequest::updateAccordingCacheMode()
166{
167 if (m_options.cache == FetchOptions::Cache::Default
168 && (m_resourceRequest.hasHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::IfModifiedSince)
169 || m_resourceRequest.hasHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::IfNoneMatch)
170 || m_resourceRequest.hasHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::IfUnmodifiedSince)
171 || m_resourceRequest.hasHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::IfMatch)
172 || m_resourceRequest.hasHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::IfRange)))
173 m_options.cache = FetchOptions::Cache::NoStore;
174
175 switch (m_options.cache) {
176 case FetchOptions::Cache::NoCache:
177 m_resourceRequest.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::RefreshAnyCacheData);
178 m_resourceRequest.addHTTPHeaderFieldIfNotPresent(HTTPHeaderName::CacheControl, HTTPHeaderValues::maxAge0());
179 break;
180 case FetchOptions::Cache::NoStore:
181 m_options.cachingPolicy = CachingPolicy::DisallowCaching;
182 m_resourceRequest.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::DoNotUseAnyCache);
183 m_resourceRequest.addHTTPHeaderFieldIfNotPresent(HTTPHeaderName::Pragma, HTTPHeaderValues::noCache());
184 m_resourceRequest.addHTTPHeaderFieldIfNotPresent(HTTPHeaderName::CacheControl, HTTPHeaderValues::noCache());
185 break;
186 case FetchOptions::Cache::Reload:
187 m_resourceRequest.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData);
188 m_resourceRequest.addHTTPHeaderFieldIfNotPresent(HTTPHeaderName::Pragma, HTTPHeaderValues::noCache());
189 m_resourceRequest.addHTTPHeaderFieldIfNotPresent(HTTPHeaderName::CacheControl, HTTPHeaderValues::noCache());
190 break;
191 case FetchOptions::Cache::Default:
192 break;
193 case FetchOptions::Cache::ForceCache:
194 m_resourceRequest.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataElseLoad);
195 break;
196 case FetchOptions::Cache::OnlyIfCached:
197 m_resourceRequest.setCachePolicy(ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataDontLoad);
198 break;
199 }
200}
201
202void CachedResourceRequest::updateAcceptEncodingHeader()
203{
204 if (!m_resourceRequest.hasHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::Range))
205 return;
206
207 // FIXME: rdar://problem/40879225. Media engines triggering the load should not set this Accept-Encoding header.
208 ASSERT(!m_resourceRequest.hasHTTPHeaderField(HTTPHeaderName::AcceptEncoding) || m_options.destination == FetchOptions::Destination::Audio || m_options.destination == FetchOptions::Destination::Video);
209
210 m_resourceRequest.addHTTPHeaderFieldIfNotPresent(HTTPHeaderName::AcceptEncoding, "identity"_s);
211}
212
213void CachedResourceRequest::removeFragmentIdentifierIfNeeded()
214{
215 URL url = MemoryCache::removeFragmentIdentifierIfNeeded(m_resourceRequest.url());
216 if (url.string() != m_resourceRequest.url())
217 m_resourceRequest.setURL(url);
218}

235void CachedResourceRequest::updateReferrerAndOriginHeaders(FrameLoader& frameLoader)
236{
237 // Implementing step 9 to 11 of https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#http-network-or-cache-fetch as of 16 March 2018
238 String outgoingReferrer = frameLoader.outgoingReferrer();
239 if (m_resourceRequest.hasHTTPReferrer())
240 outgoingReferrer = m_resourceRequest.httpReferrer();
241 updateRequestReferrer(m_resourceRequest, m_options.referrerPolicy, outgoingReferrer);
242
243 if (!m_resourceRequest.httpOrigin().isEmpty())
244 return;
245 String outgoingOrigin;
246 if (m_options.mode == FetchOptions::Mode::Cors)
247 outgoingOrigin = SecurityOrigin::createFromString(outgoingReferrer)->toString();
248 else
249 outgoingOrigin = SecurityPolicy::generateOriginHeader(m_options.referrerPolicy, m_resourceRequest.url(), SecurityOrigin::createFromString(outgoingReferrer));
250 FrameLoader::addHTTPOriginIfNeeded(m_resourceRequest, outgoingOrigin);
251}

253void CachedResourceRequest::updateUserAgentHeader(FrameLoader& frameLoader)
254{
255 frameLoader.applyUserAgentIfNeeded(m_resourceRequest);
256}
257
258bool isRequestCrossOrigin(SecurityOrigin* origin, const URL& requestURL, const ResourceLoaderOptions& options)
259{
260 if (!origin)
261 return false;
262
263 // Using same origin mode guarantees the loader will not do a cross-origin load, so we let it take care of it and just return false.
264 if (options.mode == FetchOptions::Mode::SameOrigin)
265 return false;
266
267 // FIXME: We should remove options.sameOriginDataURLFlag once https://github.com/whatwg/fetch/issues/393 is fixed.
268 if (requestURL.protocolIsData() && options.sameOriginDataURLFlag == SameOriginDataURLFlag::Set)
269 return false;
270
271 return !origin->canRequest(requestURL);
272}
273
274void CachedResourceRequest::setDestinationIfNotSet(FetchOptions::Destination destination)
275{
276 if (m_options.destination != FetchOptions::Destination::EmptyString)
277 return;
278 m_options.destination = destination;
279}

282void CachedResourceRequest::setClientIdentifierIfNeeded(DocumentIdentifier clientIdentifier)
283{
284 if (!m_options.clientIdentifier)
285 m_options.clientIdentifier = clientIdentifier;
286}
287
288void CachedResourceRequest::setSelectedServiceWorkerRegistrationIdentifierIfNeeded(ServiceWorkerRegistrationIdentifier identifier)
289{
290 if (isNonSubresourceRequest(m_options.destination))
291 return;
292 if (isPotentialNavigationOrSubresourceRequest(m_options.destination))
293 return;
294
295 if (m_options.serviceWorkersMode == ServiceWorkersMode::None)
296 return;
297 if (m_options.serviceWorkerRegistrationIdentifier)
298 return;
299
300 m_options.serviceWorkerRegistrationIdentifier = identifier;
301}
302
303void CachedResourceRequest::setNavigationServiceWorkerRegistrationData(const std::optional<ServiceWorkerRegistrationData>& data)
304{
305 if (!data || !data->activeWorker) {
306 m_options.serviceWorkersMode = ServiceWorkersMode::None;
307 return;
308 }
309 m_options.serviceWorkerRegistrationIdentifier = data->identifier;
310}
311#endif
